  }, "To this day all modern computers have two major compute components (CPU and GPU) and two \u201Cstorage\u201D components (Random Access Memory and Mass Storage \u2014 hdd/ssd).\nRAM is often lumped with \u201Ccompute\u201D, but not because it does any computations on its own (it most definitely is storing data), but because CPU is absolutely\nuseless without it. All other peripherals are mostly irrelevant commodity."), mdx("li", {
